<HEADLINE>
FT  08 MAR 94 / London Stock Exchange: Other big moves
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By CHRISTOPHER PRICE, JOEL KIBAZO, PETER JOHN and STEVE THOMPSON
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
An announcement by Northern Leisure that its accounts are to receive an
Pounds 8.5m boost, together with positive remarks on current trading, pushed
the shares 10 ahead to 51p.
USM-quoted Cupid, the manufacturer of bridal wear, lost favour in the
marketplace after the board issued a profits warning and the shares plunged
6 to a new low of 16p. Cupid said it would be 'substantially loss-making' in
the current financial period.
