<HEADLINE>
FT  08 MAR 94 / World Commodities Prices: Tea
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
There was good but irregular demand, reports the Tea Brokers' Association.
Brightest and good medium east Africans were 5 to 15p easier except Pekoe
Dusts which moved higher. Mediums opened fully firm but tended easier
towards the close. Plainer descriptions sold well and often advanced.
Ceylons met good competition but prices were generally lower. Offshore: good
general demand at fully firm to dearer rates. Quality 190p/kg, good medium
140p/kg, medium 123p/kg, low medium 90p/kg. The highest price realised this
week was 221p/kg for a Rwanda pf. 1.
