FT  08 MAR 94 / International Company News: Rabobank
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By RONALD VAN DE KROL
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   AMSTERDAM
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Rabobank, the big Dutch co-operative bank, reported a 10 per cent increase
in 1993 net profit to Fl 1.1bn (Dollars 570m) and predicted a further
improvement in 1994, writes Ronald van de Krol in Amsterdam.
Lending expanded 9 per cent last year. Funds entrusted to the bank by
account holders grew by only 2.3 per cent, which Rabobank attributed partly
to a growing interest in other types of investments following the general
decline in interest rates.
