             German airline.
 -Sept 92:   BA buys 49.9% of TAT, French regional carrier based at
             Paris Orly, from where TAT has started international
             operations in BA colours. Cost: Pounds 15m
 -Nov 92:    BA pays pounds 1m for virtually bankrupt Gatwick-based
             Dan-Air. Cost: Pounds 45m (in debt and other liabilities
             taken on)
 -Jan 93:    BA gains stake in USAir via purchase of convertible
             preference shares with 24.6% voting rights. Stake
             maintained through support of rights issue. Cost: Pounds
             265m (pounds 189m plus pounds 67m)
