<HEADLINE>
FT  08 MAR 94 / College lecturer wins race bias case
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By LISA WOOD
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
A technical college carried out institutional discrimination and
victimisation 'in the truest sense' against a black lecturer, an industrial
tribunal has ruled, Lisa Wood writes.
The Commission for Racial Equality said yesterday that Mr Stanley Jenkins'
complaints of racial abuse from students were disbelieved by Thanet
Technical College in Broadstairs, Kent. When Mr Jenkins started industrial
tribunal proceedings under the Race Relations Act the college started an
inquiry into his teaching performance.
The tribunal said: 'It was a manifestly unfair attempt to put pressure on Mr
Jenkins to curtail his proceedings.'
The award for damages to Mr Jenkins, who is still employed by the college,
has yet to be set.
