<TEXT>
Davy International, part of Trafalgar House of the UK, said yesterday it had
won a contract worth about Pounds 75m to design and supply a blast furnace
for China Steel in Kaohsiung, Taiwan.
The contract was awarded after more than two years of technical and
commercial discussions with China Steel, in the face of intense competition
from Japan and Germany.
