<HEADLINE>
FT  08 MAR 94 / Moldovans reject Romania tie
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By JILL BARSHAY
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   KIEV
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Moldovans overwhelmingly rejected a 50-year-old nationalist aspiration to
reunite with Romania in a national plebiscite on Sunday. Moldovans were
asked whether they supported 'an independent Moldova within its 1990
borders, which maintains neutrality, establishes ties with other nations and
provides equal rights for all citizens.' Of the two-thirds of the electorate
who voted, 90 per cent voted Yes to the question. President Mircea Snegur
hopes to use the result to lure back the breakaway republic of Trans-Dnestr,
which believes that Moldova, 60 per cent populated by ethnic Romanians, is
intent on reuniting with Romania.
