<HEADLINE>
FT  08 MAR 94 / EU moves on night work
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By GILLIAN TETT
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   BRUSSELS
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
The European Commission yesterday threatened Belgium, France, Greece, Italy
and Portugal with legal action over their restrictions on night work for
women when a ban did not exist on night work by men. The commission said it
had written to all five governments requesting that they change their
legislation to bring it into line with a 1991 EU ruling which judged that
banning night work by women, but not by men, was discriminatory. If the
governments do not comply, it will take them to the European Court of
Justice.
