<HEADLINE>
FT  08 MAR 94 / Russia-Ukraine gas row talks
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By JOHN LLOYD
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   MOSCOW
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Russian and Ukrainian officials are to meet in Moscow tomorrow to discuss a
dispute over gas supplies to Ukraine which has strained relations between
the two states and raised fears over the security of Russian gas supplies to
western Europe. Gazprom, the Russian monopoly supplier of gas, said
yesterday it would maintain supplies to Ukraine at between 50m and 80m cu
metres a day - enough to keep houses heated, but not enough for industry.
Gazprom officials say Ukraine is taking extra supplies from the west
European pipeline, but Ukraine said the 200m cu metres a day it was
distributing was coming from Russian supplies and storage. The dispute is
over an unpaid bill claimed by Gazprom to be running at Rbs1,500bn.
</TEXT>
