<HEADLINE>
FT  07 MAR 94 / International Company News: Generali premium income rises
13.5%
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By JOHN SIMKINS
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   MILAN
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Aggregate premium income at Generali, Italy's biggest insurance company,
rose 13.5 per cent to L19,200bn (Dollars 11.3bn) in 1993 after a further
strong performance from its joint venture in Spain with Banco Central
Hispanoamericano, according to preliminary results, writes John Simkins in
Milan.
Generali said the parent company's net profits, which will be revealed after
a board meeting in early May, were expected to show an improvement on the
L389.8bn in 1992 in spite of a heavier tax burden. The parent company's
premium income was L9,550bn, an increase of 8.4 per cent. Adjusted for
currency factors, the rise was 4.3 per cent.
