Share prices of companies controlled by Toronto's Bronfman family jumped
late last week in the wake of reports that Anglo American of South Africa
was negotiating to acquire a large stake in the Canadian resources, real
estate and financial services empire.
Anglo American and the Bronfman group declined to comment, which suggested
that the South African conglomerate might invest an initial CDollars 300m
