interested in Noranda, the Toronto-based mining, forestry and energy group.
Noranda shares gained CDollars 1.25 last week to CDollars 26.25.
Mr Alf Powis, Noranda's chairman, said that 'there have been conversations
between the (Bronfman) group and Anglo American.'
However, Mr Powis said he was under the impression that the contacts had
been terminated.
