With impeccable timing - just as the country's latest economic stabilisation
plan seems ready to expire - a flood of British bigwigs are zapping into
Brazil to size up investment prospects.
Michael Portillo, the Treasury chief secretary, has come trailing banking
and industry worthies. When Portillo goes, air chief marshal Sir Michael
