<HEADLINE>
FT  07 MAR 94 / De-regulation bill proposal could backfire on employers
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
A proposal in the government's de-regulation bill to allow companies to
select employees for redundancy - contravening customary arrangements such
as last-in, first-out - could backfire on employers that use it as an excuse
to abandon redundancy procedures, says the Institute of Personnel
Management's vice-president for employee relations.
In today's issue of the IPM's magazine, Mr Ewart Wooldridge says that the
measure could be seen by employers as an invitation to reject a structured
and consultative approach to redundancy.
'There is a substantial pay-off from treating staff and their
representatives properly. Those who remain will judge you by how you looked
after those who had to leave.'
</TEXT>
